result.execSummary:
The defendant Harold EB Rodriguez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Misappropriate ID Info - Avoid Penalty, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.201(2)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.

Defendant is prohibited from being in possession of any personal identifying information that is not his own. No contact with S. Kehayias or L. Kehayias directly or indirectly. No phone calls , e-mails, text messages, written communications or by third party.

Defendant must obtain and possess valid identification. Defendant must report any change in physical and mailing address to the District Attorney's Office within 48 hours of any change being made. Defendant must take every effort necessary to rectify any and all issues created by using the victim's identity. Any other terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by supervising agent. DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

timeConds.notes: Defendant is entitled to work release privileges. No Good Time Credit. Sentence to commence forthwith.
